<P><H1 align=center>DC280 – ADD/EDIT LEGAL REPRESENTATIVE DETAILS</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red>Areas shown in red text are mandatory 
and must be completed to proceed.</FONT>            </P>
<P><H3>Company name: </H3>The directory search button will 
take you to a screen that allows you to search for the name of the company you 
want to input. Input the name of the company and click on directory search. 
Select the company when shown and click on ‘Select’, this will transfer the 
details already held to the details screen. If the company name is not on the 
Directory search, you will need to type it in the field manually.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Is in the directory: </H3>Click ‘No’ if the company is 
not in the search directory.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Different legal rep for lender: </H3>Is the 
solicitor/legal representative used by the applicant the same as the lender’s 
solicitor/legal representative.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Solicitor status: </H3>What is the solicitors status on 
the lenders panel, eg; are they permanent or temporary for the duration of the 
application.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Address: </H3>If the company is found in the directory 
search, the address fields of the branch will be automatically populated. If 
not, input the post code and click on the <STRONG>P.A.F search </STRONG>button. 
Select the address required and click on <STRONG>Select</STRONG>, this will 
populate the address in the relevant address fields. Click on the <STRONG>Clear 
</STRONG>button to delete all address fields.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Contact details: </H3>Input all details known, once 
completed you can add the address and contact details to the directory by 
clicking on the <STRONG>Add to directory </STRONG>button.
<P></P>
<P>Click <STRONG>OK </STRONG>  when all details completed.</P>
